<p>I wrote a YouTube plugin for CKEditor 4.5.3. Now I'm trying to setup custom context menu without default items such as cut, copy, paste, edit iFrame, and leave only custom ones (editVideoYoutubeItem, removeVideoYoutubeItem). The iFrame Item, was successfully removed by disabling iFrame plugin in configuration:</p>  <pre><code>/**  * Remove some default Plugins  *   * @see http://ckeditor.com/forums/CKEditor-3.x/How-add-new-items-ContextMenu  * @see http://docs.ckeditor.com/#!/api/CKEDITOR.config-cfg-removePlugins      */ config.removePlugins = 'iframe'; </code></pre>  <p>But I can not remove other ones (pastetext,clipboard) because I need them for other stuff. Here is the code of Context Menu:</p>  <pre><code>// Adding Context Menu Support if (editor.contextMenu) {     editor.addMenuGroup('videoYoutubeGroup');      editor.addMenuItems(     {         'editVideoYoutubeItem' : {             label   : editor.lang.videoyoutube.menuitems.edit,             icon    : iconPath,             command : 'videoYoutubeDialog',             group   : 'videoYoutubeGroup',             order   : 1         }     });      // Code creating context menu items goes here.     editor.contextMenu.addListener(function(element)     {         if(element)         {                            element = element.getAscendant('div', true);                         }         if(element &amp;&amp; element.hasClass('embed-responsive') &amp;&amp; !element.isReadOnly() &amp;&amp; !element.data('cke-realelement'))         {             return {                 editVideoYoutubeItem    : CKEDITOR.TRISTATE_OFF             };         }         return null;     }); } </code></pre>  <p>I found a method removeAll() in API (<a href="http://docs.ckeditor.com/#!/api/CKEDITOR.plugins.contextMenu" rel="nofollow">http://docs.ckeditor.com/#!/api/CKEDITOR.plugins.contextMenu</a>), but can't figure out how to use it.</p>  <p>Any assistance would be appreciated. Thanks in advance.</p>